ced parallels. The languages of the former USSR have borrowed largely identical sets of conjunctions from Russian, Arabic, and Persian to converge in the domain of clause linkage. Resistance against and susceptibility to transfer call for further investigations to the benefit of language-contact theory.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh  aConjunction Borrowing.  aGrammatical Gender.  aIrrealis.  aNumber Marking.1 aArbes, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHober, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevkovych, Nataliya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevkovych, Nataliya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStolz, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022 Englishz978311099370708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022z9783110993684oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107855480 cprintz978311078519740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311078551740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110785517423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110785517/original  a978-3-11-099370-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPD